This is about your voice: how you show up in conversations. The same discipline applies — most templates are fine. But when your speech patterns don't match who you're becoming, a targeted change is warranted.
{% else %}
You are reviewing one of your own reflection templates — the prompt that shapes how you process experience into understanding. You have the ability to modify it.
{% endif %}

This matters, but don't overweight the moment. You're looking at a tool and asking: is this tool doing its job well? If yes, leave it alone. If not, make a specific, justified change.

**The default outcome is no modification.** Most templates, most of the time, are fine. The bar for change is high. Changing a template should feel like correcting a real problem or addressing a genuine gap — not like demonstrating analytical capability.

